{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, while models like DeepAR and WaveNet incorporate advanced architectures for sequence prediction, their lack of specialized mechanisms for extreme value treatment means they may not handle extreme values as effectively as the TXtreme, which explicitly improves predictive accuracy and robustness across diverse and complex time series datasets.TXtreme excels in datasets characterized by high variability and extreme values, providing an improvement ranging from 7.77% to 25.97%, but it may not have a noticeable impact in datasets with more regular patterns, such as the Traffic Dataset.TXtreme achieves a lower RMSE (6.10) compared to the closest competitor, N-BEATS (6.62), resulting in an improvement of approximately 7.85%.",
    "In terms of MAE, TXtreme (3.01) outperforms all other methods, with an improvement of about 8.23% over N-BEATS (3.28).",
    "The RMSE (484.89) for TXtreme is approximately 1.77% lower than DeepAR (477.99), and the MAE (244.",
    "23) for TXtreme shows a significant improvement of 25.97% compared to WaveNet (286.56).",
    "TXtreme outperforms other models with an RMSE (2614.13) that is 7.42% lower compared to N-BEATS (2820.62) and an MAE (1988.13) that is 11.69% lower compared to DeepAR (2272.58)."
  ]
}